3.Given a number n, find the last digit of the nth Fibonacci number. The Fibonacci sequence is a series in which each number is the sum of the previous two numbers, where F(0) = 0, F(1) = 1, and F(n) = F(n-1) + F(n-2) for n >= 2.
Platform : GeeksForGeeks
SOURCE CODE :class Solution {
    static int fib(int n) {
        if(n==0)return 0;
         if(n==1)return 1;
         int a=0,b=1,c;
         for(int i=2;i<=n;i++){
      c=(a+b)%10;
             a=b;b=c;
         }
       return b;
    }
}
